## C++ Client Management System

A simple Client Management System written in C++ for learning purposes.
This project demonstrates file handling, structures, vectors, and string parsing in C++.


This program manages client records stored in a text file (Clients.txt) and provides a full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) system.

It loads all clients into a vector of structs (strInfo) and offers functions to:

Convert text lines to client records and vice versa.

Add new clients with unique account numbers.

Display all clients in a formatted table.

Search for clients by account number and view details.

Update client information safely.

Delete clients after confirmation, marking them in memory and updating the file.

This project is useful for practicing structs, file handling, vectors, string parsing, user input validation, and safe delete/update operations.



